    },
    {
      "id": "88b66f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Greek major is designed to identify and analyze ancient classical documents, material evidence, or other forms of primary sources and demonstrate their critical skills by engaging in presentations and weekly discourse with their peers. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, at minimum, you must complete the following courses by the end of the spring before transfer: One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language. Completion of two years of college level foreign language is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// classics.ucla.edu .and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: The community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\";\">The Greek major is designed to identify and analyze ancient classical documents, material evidence, or other forms of primary sources and demonstrate their critical skills by engaging in presentations and weekly discourse with their peers.</span></p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, at minimum, you must complete the following courses by the end of the spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level coursework in the declared language OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared language.</li></ul><p>Completion of two years of college level foreign language is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>. A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.classics.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">classics.ucla.edu</a>.and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: The community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    }
